Act I
Rogue Encampment

The Rogue Encampment is a makeshift town located right next to the Blood Moor. As its name designates, it is the camp set up by the survivors of the battle at the Rogue Monastery.

​

NPCs:  Akara,  Charsi,  Deckard Cain,  Gheed,  Kashya, and  Warriv.

 

Quests:  Den of Evil,  Sister's Burial Grounds,  The Search for Cain, The Forgotten Tower,  Tools of the Trade,  and Sisters of the Slaughter.  

Quest:

Find The Den of Evil

Blood Moor

There are four potential spawn points for the Den, I usually just run a circle around Blood Moor until I find it.

Area Foe:

Zombie, Quill Rat, and Fallen

Quest:

The Den of Evil

The Den of Evil

The Den of Evil is home to the first quest in your long journey to fight and defeat the Prime Evils through Sanctuary.

Area Foe:

Zombie, Fallen, Fallen Shaman, Gargantuan Beast, and Corpsefire

Quest:

​

Cold Plains

The Cold Plains is home to The Cave, and is the only way into The Burial Grounds. Other then that this is just a pass through zone.

Area Foe:

Fallen, Fallen Shaman, Gargantuan Beast, Dark Hunter, Dark Spearwoman, and Bishibosh

Quest:

​

The Cave Level I

​

Area Foe:

Fallen, Fallen Shaman, Skeleton, Hungry Dead, Dark Ranger, and Coldcrow

Quest:

​

The Cave Level II

​

Area Foe:

Fallen, Fallen Shaman, Skeleton, Hungry Dead, Dark Ranger, and Coldcrow

Quest:

Sister's Burial Ground

The Burial Grounds

It is home to Blood Raven, and two side areas, The Crypt and Mausoleum, which neither of those place have anything special about them.

Area Foe:

Blood Raven

Quest:

The Search for Cain (Part 2)

Stony Fields

This is also where you will find the entrance to the Undergound Passage (3 spawn points) and the entrance to Tristram (After part one of the quest), You will need to find the Cairn Stones after you have found the Scroll of Inifuss

Area Foe:

Fallen, Fallen Shaman, Carver, Skeleton, Hungry Dead, Dark Ranger, Foul Crow, Foul Crow Nest, Moon Clan, and Rakanishu

Quest:

​

The Underground Passage Level I

The Underground passage is a cave network that leads you to the Dark Woods. It is the only connection between Stony Fields and The Dark Woods

Area Foe:

Fallen, Fallen Shaman, Carver, Skeleton Archer, Misshapen, Vile Hunter

Quest:

​

The Underground Passage Level II

This second level contains a chest, but really isn't worth farming

Area Foe:

Fallen, Fallen Shaman, Carver, Skeleton Archer, Misshapen, Vile Hunter

Quest:

The Search for Cain (Part 1)

The Dark Wood

The Dark Wood is where you'll begin your "Search for Cain" quest. It is the location of the first of many "Hidden Ubers".

Area Foe:

Carver, Carver Shaman, Skeleton Archer, Vile Lancer, Vile Hunter, Spike Fiend, Brute, and Treehead Woodfist

Quest:

​

The Black Marsh

The Black Marsh is home to the Forgotten Tower, which is the next quest on your journey, along with The Hole Level I & II. It is a location of a "Hidden Uber"

Area Foe:

Carver, Carver Shaman, Blood Hawk, Blood Hawk Nest, Vile Archer, Night Clan, Returned, Brute

Quest:

​

The Forgotten Tower Level I

The Tower has been scaled back on this mod. Going from five levels, down to three. This makes this part of the play through more streamlined.

Area Foe:

Blood Clan, Dark Archer, Ghost, Devilkin

Quest:

​

The Forgotten Tower Level II

Keep going deeper, your almost there!

Area Foe:

Blood Clan, Dark Archer, Ghost, Devilkin

Quest:

The Forgotten Tower

The Forgotten Tower Level III

This is the last level of the Tower, kill The Countess and get out! But not before opening her chest!

Area Foe:

Blood Clan, Dark Archer, Dark Stalker (minion), Ghost, Devilkin, and The Countess

Quest:

​

The Hole Level I

There really is nothing to say about this, or level two. Nothing to see here. Don't waste your time

Area Foe:

Misshapen, Vile Archer, Carver, Carver Shaman, Brute

Quest:

​

The Hole Level II

Again, nothing to see here. No reason to come down this far.

Area Foe:

Misshapen, Vile Archer, Carver, Carver Shaman, Brute

Quest:

​

Tamoe Highlands

Past the Black Marsh lies the Tamoe Highland, the final open wilderness area before reaching the Rogues' Monastery. It is a location of a "Hidden Uber"

Area Foe:

Returned Archer, Returned Mage, Thorn Beast, Dark Lancer, Dark Stalker, Devilkin, Carver, Carver Shaman

Quest:

​

The Pit Level I

Unlike in Diablo 2, The Pit Level I & II are not very good farming spots. Its best just to pass this up

Area Foe:

Devilkin, Devilkin Shaman, Dark Stalker, Dark Archer, Bone Warrior

Quest:

​

The Pit Level II

Like its counterpart, The Pit Level II is just not worth farming. There is a chest down here, but that's it.

Area Foe:

Devilkin, Devilkin Shaman, Dark Stalker, Dark Archer, Bone Warrior

Quest:

​

Outer Cloister

The Outer Cloister holds the entrance to the Barracks. The Barracks can spawn in all three locations.

Area Foe:

Black Rogue, Yeti, Razor Spine, Devilkin, Devilkin Shaman

Quest:

Tools of the Trade

Barracks

The Barracks is where the Smith resides. There is also three potential spawn points for Jail Level I

Area Foe:

Devilkin, Devilkin Shaman, Death Clan, Bone Mage, Bone Archer, Black Rogue, and The Smith

Quest:

​

Jail Level I

The Jail is quite similar to the Barracks, but tend to be a little darker, and of course full of more dangerous enemies. Nothing to see here, move through quickly

Area Foe:

Bone Mage, Bone Archer, Death Clan, Wraith, Dark One

Quest:

​

Jail Level II

Nothing but monsters here, so best you keep moving on.

Area Foe:

Bone Mage, Bone Archer, Death Clan, Wraith, Dark One

Quest:

​

Inner Cloister & Cathedral

The short path between Jail Level II & The Catacombs. The Catacombs has two spawn locations here.

Area Foe:

Wraith, Dark One, Dark Shaman, Tainted, and Bone Ash

Quest:

​

Catacombs Level I

The last stretch of zones before the end of Act I, Level II can spawn in one of the four corners

Area Foe:

Tainted, Dark One, Dark Shaman, Rat Man

Quest:

​

Catacombs Level II

You are almost there! One more to go! Level three has four potential spawn points as well.

Area Foe:

Tainted, Dark One, Dark Shaman, Rat Man

Quest:

Sisters to the Slaughter

Catacombs Level III

The home to Andariel herself. You made it, kill her!

Area Foe:

Tainted, Dark One, Dark Shaman, Rat Man, and Andariel
